{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"68ab40dc-0408-45f2-837e-927b8ec59801","content":"Here are the changes needed:\n\n**1. Update your `.csproj` properties:**\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>\n  <!-- enables `dotnet test` integration with the new platform -->\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**2. Update NuGet packages:**\n- **Keep** `NUnit` and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (update to latest).\n- **Keep** `NUnit3TestAdapter` but update to **5.0+** (adds MTP support).\n- **Add** `NUnit.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform` — this is the runner/adapter bridge for the new platform.\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.*\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit\" Version=\"4.*\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"5.*\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `OutputType Exe` is required because tests now run as a self-contained executable, not via `vstest.console`.\n- Your test code and `[Test]` attributes stay the same — no source changes needed.\n- `dotnet test` continues to work thanks to `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ec6a70fd-ca46-484a-a04d-1a18817cab87","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question — I don't need to explore a codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.\n\nKey steps for migrating NUnit from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. Update NUnit3TestAdapter to version 5.0+ (which supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform)\n2. Add `NUnit.Runner` package (the MTP runner for NUnit)\n3. Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (VSTest infrastructure)\n4. Add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` to the project\n\n\n5. Enable the testing platform by setting `<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` in your project file\n\nActually, I should clarify the exact migration path — NUnit3TestAdapter 4.6.0 is the VSTest adapter, but for Microsoft.Testing.Platform support you'll want to use `NUnit.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform` instead, and you can keep `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` since it's compatible with the newer approach. I need to clarify the exact package names and configuration properties for NUnit migration. The adapter is distributed as `NUnit.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform` (available in NUnit3TestAdapter 5.0+), and I need to set both `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` and `<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` in the project file.","outputTokens":1146,"requestId":"CFE4:12ABA3:629EC1D:6DCD99E:69EC0E42"},"id":"cc704563-8160-44c7-91b1-9c31b5e2b11a","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:44:07.027Z","parentId":"4fd7402b-f40f-49da-a421-4c1492d6b83e"}
